default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultRevised Select Committee Core Tasks for Departmental Select Committees
default&#xa0;
defaultOverall aim: To hold Ministers and Departments to account for their policy and decision-making and to support the House in its control of the supply of public money and scrutiny of legislation 
defaultSTRATEGY 
defaultTask 1 To examine the strategy of the department, how it has identified its key objectives and priorities and whether it has the means to achieve them, in terms of plans, resources, skills, capabilities and management information 
defaultPOLICY 
defaultTask 2 To examine policy proposals by the department, and areas of emerging policy, or where existing policy is deficient, and make proposals 
defaultEXPENDITURE AND PERFORMANCE 
defaultTask 3 To examine the expenditure plans, outturn and performance of the department and its arm's length bodies, and the relationships between spending and delivery of outcomes 
defaultDRAFT BILLS 
defaultTask 4 To conduct scrutiny of draft bills within the committee's responsibilities 
defaultBILLS AND DELEGATED LEGISLATION 
defaultTask 5 To assist the House in its consideration of bills and statutory instruments, including draft orders under the Public Bodies Act 
defaultPOST-LEGISLATIVE SCRUTINY 
defaultTask 6 To examine the implementation of legislation and scrutinise the department's post- legislative assessments 
defaultEUROPEAN SCRUTINY 
defaultTask 7 To scrutinise policy developments at the European level and EU legislative proposals 
defaultAPPOINTMENTS 
defaultTask 8 To scrutinise major appointments made by the department and to hold pre-appointment hearings where appropriate 
defaultSUPPORT FOR THE HOUSE 
defaultTask 9 To produce timely reports to inform debate in the House, including Westminster Hall, or debating committees, and to examine petitions tabled 
defaultPUBLIC ENGAGEMENT 
defaultTask 10 To assist the House of Commons in better engaging with the public by ensuring that the work of the committee is accessible to the public 
